physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Ventricular preexcitation noted on resting ECG at age 2. Recent 2D echocardiography showed normal left ventricular function, interventricular septal thickness of 9 mm, and maximal LV free wall thickness of 11 mm.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The patient has had recurrent syncopal events since age 2, progressing to chronic atrial fibrillation since age 15 and remains dependent on ventricular pacing.
